title: O.J. Made in America (720p) Part 1-5 Complete
description:
O.J.: Made in America is a 2016 American five-part documentary miniseries (464 minutes long) directed and produced by Ezra Edelman for ESPN Films and their 30 for 30 series. The documentary explores two of America's greatest fixations â€“ race and celebrity â€“ through the life of O. J. Simpson. It starts with his emerging football career at the University of Southern California, and why America fell in love with him. Then it covers O.J. being accused of murdering Nicole Brown Simpson and Ronald Goldman, the trial, his acquittal, and the events that followed. Finally, O.J.'s life for the 13 years after his acquittal is revealed, including the 2007 crime for which he is now in jail.

O.J.: Made in America premiered at the Sundance Film Festival on 22 January 2016, and debuted on ABC on 11 June 2016 as a five-part miniseries that continued on ESPN. It has received wide-spread acclaim.
